<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Non-replaced inline-block elements in normal flow with auto width</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#inlineblock-width" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="If width computes to auto then the used value width is 'shrink-to-fit'." />
        <style type="text/css">
            div
            {
                display: inline-block;
                width: auto;
                background-color: orange;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the background color starts and stops where the content does.</p>
        <div>Filler Text Filler Text Filler Text </div>
    </body>
</html>